      "amo:hasPoeticEpistemologicalFunction": {
        "@value": "The Self-Implicative Method functions as the methodological field in which the concepts, artworks, documents, metadata, graphs, and relations of the A.M.O. may be formulated, documented, and reinscribed. Even concepts that have not yet been named or textually stabilized potentially participate in its operation.",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "amo:syntheticFormula": {
        "@value": "The Self-Implicative Method designates the artistic-epistemological practice through which the artist deliberately intervenes in the contemporary regimes of existence of their own work, recognizing that documentation, cataloguing, circulation, ontologies, metadata, and algorithmic systems no longer merely describe it, but actively participate in its historicity, recoverability, and public intelligibility. Critical reinscription in these devices constitutes, in itself, a continuation of artistic practice and a form of thought production.",
        "@language": "en"
      },
